race.comment: GOSPEL GIRL (15) returned from a 19-week spell and looked home and hosed only for PRESS LINK to jump out of the ground in the final strides of a BM78 over this course and distance last start. Very good second-up performer who is up in grade but drops 3kgs. Great chance to go one better. IRON MAN (5) opened this prep with a couple of wins in country/provincial NSW then struggled in a better race at Rosehill a fortnight ago. Distance specialist who is back in a winnable race today. JONNY DA WOLF (6) settled near the tail and was never in contention last time out over this trip at the Sunshine Coast. Down a touch in grade and has been in the money at four of five Eagle Farm runs. Solid each-way hope. PRESS LINK (8) returned from Hong Kong and a 13-month spell with a barnstorming win here at this trip recently. Queensland Guineas placegetter two season back. Can win again without surprising. FACUNDO (13) resumes. Has won five from nine but usually needs one run. Exotics inclusion.
